NAME
	geo-map (display) - project ndb-stanza entity and feature files through a map projection and draw graticule, vector features, and affiliation-coloured glyphs

INTERFACE
	display (MatrixDisplay)

READS
	entities/		directory; one file per entity
	entities/<name>	ndb stanza: id= lat= lon= affil= kind= label=
			course= (lat/lon required; entity skipped otherwise)
	features/		directory; one file per feature
	features/<name>	ndb stanza: id= type= points= radius= color=
			fill= width= label= (type: circle, polygon,
			polyline; points: space-separated lat,lon pairs)

MOUNT
	The outdir of a service that produces entities/ and features/
	ndb stanzas - /tmp/matrix/<service>.  With geo-fixture:
	/tmp/matrix/geo-fixture.
	Include that service in the same composition (e.g.
	`service sysmon-svc /`) so its outdir is populated.

WRITES
	none (renders only)

DESCRIPTION
	Mercator projection via geoproj.  Reloads only when a directory's
	file count or max mtime changes.  Interactive: button-1 drag
	pans, click picks the nearest entity, wheel and +/- keys zoom,
	h/j/k/l pan, f centres on the selection.  Glyph shape follows
	kind (air triangle, sea diamond, ground square); colour follows
	affiliation (friend/hostile/neutral/unknown).

SEE ALSO
	geo-fixture (produces this input format)
